parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drag link or steering system can cause the loss of directional steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or unstable
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the drag link or steering components are loose or broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The power steering pump fails
the steering becomes heavy or difficult
the power steering fluid leaks or is low.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failures can cause the vehicle to lose power or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The transmission shifts harshly or erratically
the transmission slips or hesitates
the transmission fails to engage or disengage gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recall repair for the steering system can cause alignment issues, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, and can also lead to uneven tire wear.
symptoms: The vehicle's alignment is off after the recall repair
the steering wheel is not centered
the tires wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fan shroud can cause the fan to break off, leading to a loss of coolant and engine power, and potentially causing a loss of power steering and brakes.
symptoms: The fan shroud breaks or fails
the fan blade breaks off
the coolant leaks or is low.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing a fire.
symptoms: The water pump fails
the engine overheats
the coolant leaks or is low.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission solenoid can cause the vehicle to shift erratically, lose power, and become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting gears
the transmission warning light is illuminated
and the vehicle may lose power or become stuck in gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking pawl can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, even when the transmission is in park, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly
even when the transmission is in park
and the parking brake may not engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the turbo actuator electronic control can cause the engine to lose power and the vehicle to become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine loses power
the turbo actuator warning light is illuminated
and the vehicle may enter "limp mode" to protect the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in throttle response can cause the vehicle to hesitate or lag when accelerating, which can lead to accidents or near-misses, especially when merging into traffic or changing lanes.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or lags when accelerating
and there is a delay in throttle response.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while in motion, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down while in motion
the engine dies
the horn does not operate
the windows do not raise or lower
the radio does not turn off
the backup camera fails
the navigation system does not track the vehicle properly
the key fobs fail to work
the UConnect application on the phone fails to work
the vehicle says the key fob is not present when it is.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the engine to die while in motion, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine dies while in motion
the key fob is not recognized
the ignition switch is faulty
the vehicle stalls or shuts down while in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle can catch fire while parked or in motion, leading to a risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle spontaneously catches fire
the dashboard melts or burns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The wiring harness is damaged
the fuel tank is pinched
the rear ABS sensor fails
the backup camera fails
the radio fails to work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The radio fails to work
the navigation system does not track the vehicle properly
the UConnect application on the phone fails to work.
